modules.description: This module executes the x86 CPUID instruction to detect CPU vendors, model information, and feature flags. It returns data as typed values, including vendor identifiers like `Intel`, feature flags such as `SSE4_2` or `AVX2`, and CPU model details as integer triples. Use cases include runtime CPU capability checks for optimized code paths, virtualization detection via `HYPERVISOR`, and determining core counts with `cores`.
